Samsung has included references to four Galaxy S10 models in the first beta of Android 9.0 on the Galaxy S9+, Forbes reported. XDA Developers discovered configuration files in the beta upgrade that contain the names beyond0, beyond1, beyond2, and beyond2 5G. Sammobile recently reported that Samsung mobile CEO DJ Koh told Chinese media there will be “very significant” changes to the design of the Galaxy S10. He didn’t offer any details, other than that the Galaxy S10 will be available in “amazing” colours. Forbes reported that supply chain leaks from a variety of sources have revealed the Galaxy S10 range will feature a triple-lens rear camera, “ultrasonic” in-display fingerprint reader, 5G support, and an upgrade to its facial recognition functionality.